bes%20from%20Dubai-based%20businessman%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20to%20ask%20questions%20in%20parliament.%20The%20complaint%20said%20Moitra%20had%20shared%20the%20password%20of%20the%20official%20email%20of%20her%20Lok%20Sabha%20account%20with%20Hiranandani%2C%20claiming%20it%20had%20compromised%20%E2%80%98national%20security%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoitra%2C%20a%20vocal%20critic%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20had%20shot%20back%20at%20Dubey%2C%20stating%20that%20his%20complaint%20was%20because%20of%20her%20questioning%20him%20in%20parliament%20about%20a%20fake%20degree%20he%20allegedly%20submitted%20along%20with%20his%20election%20affidavit%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThursday%E2%80%99s%20meeting%20went%20on%20for%20about%20three%20hours%2C%20ending%20in%20a%20walkout%20not%20just%20by%20Moitra%20but%20also%20by%20five%20members%20belonging%20to%20the%20opposition%20parties.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20because%20she%20was%20asked%20irrelevant%2C%20indecent%20and%20unethical%20questions.%20We%20objected%20that%20such%20questions%20should%20not%20be%20asked%20by%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20member%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Asked%20what%20those%20questions%20were%2C%20the%20member%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CShe%20was%20asked%20which%20hotel%20in%20Dubai%20she%20had%20stayed%20during%20her%20visits%20and%20with%20whom%2C%20etc.%20Opposition%20members%20found%20those%20questions%20posed%20to%20a%20woman%20member%20of%20parliament%20in%20an%20official%20platform%20very%20offensive%20and%20walked%20out%20of%20it.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20member%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20meeting%20started%2C%20the%20chairperson%20began%20asking%20her%20questions%20written%20on%20a%20paper.%20What%20was%20surprising%20was%20that%20even%20after%20she%20had%20said%20a%20%E2%80%98no%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20primary%20question%2C%20parts%20of%20the%20questions%20already%20written%20on%20that%20paper%20were%20also%20asked%20by%20him%2C%20as%20if%20it%20was%20a%20task%20given%20to%20him%20that%20he%20had%20to%20mandatorily%20complete.%20Then%2C%20some%20members%20objected%20to%20the%20meeting%20starting%20with%20the%20chairperson%20questioning%20her%20because%20in%20the%20previous%20meeting%2C%20when%20Dubey%20and%20Dehadrai%20were%20called%20to%20depose%2C%20they%20were%20given%20an%20opportunity%20to%20present%20their%20opening%20statement.%20Finally%2C%20she%20was%20allowed%20to%20read%20out%20her%20statement.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20other%20member%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThroughout%20her%20statement%2C%20she%20had%20highlighted%20that%20the%20complaint%20has%20stemmed%20from%20a%20personal%20fight%20(between%20her%20and%20Dehadrai).%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAsked%20if%20she%20had%20shared%20her%20password%20with%20Hiranandani%2C%20Moitra%20admitted%20to%20taking%20help%20from%20his%20personal%20staff%20to%20file%20questions%20in%20parliament.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20this%2C%20some%20members%20pointed%20out%20to%20the%20chairperson%20that%20most%20MPs%20take%20help%20from%20others%20to%20file%20questions%20online%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20member%20related.%20All%20the%20questions%20posed%20to%20the%20TMC%20were%20only%20by%20the%20chairperson%20and%20no%20other%20member%20was%20allowed%20to%20ask%20questions%2C%20the%20member%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Sonkar%20accused%20the%20opposition%20members%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbehaving%20unethically%E2%80%9D%20before%20walking%20out.%20He%20claimed%20that%20Moitra%20became%20angry%20and%20used%20unparliamentary%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20the%20meeting%20ended%20with%20a%20walkout%20by%20five%20opposition%20MPs%2C%20it%20is%20not%20clear%20what%20is%20the%20next%20course%20of%20action.%20Aside%20from%20the%20chairperson%2C%20there%20were%20eleven%20members%20present%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20meeting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Demeaning%2C%20prejudiced%20behaviour%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoitra%20slammed%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20probe%20as%20%E2%80%98filthy%2C%20unethical%2C%20misogynistic%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20addressed%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20speaker%20Om%20Birla%20she%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cunethical%2C%20sordid%20and%20prejudiced%20behaviour%E2%80%9D%20was%20meted%20out%20to%20her%20at%20the%20hearing%20of%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20by%20the%20chairman.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInstead%20of%20asking%20questions%20on%20the%20pertinent%20subject%2C%20the%20chairman%20exhibited%20a%20preconceived%20bias%20by%20maliciously%20and%20clearly%20in%20a%20defamatory%20way%20questioning%20me%2C%20so%20much%20so%20that%20five%20of%20the%2011%20members%20present%20walked%20out%20and%20boycotted%20the%20proceedings%20in%20protest%20at%20his%20shameful%20conduct%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20request%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Secretariat%20to%20please%20disclose%20the%20regulations%20governing%20the%20sharing%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20password%20of%20the%20portal%20to%20merely%20type%20out%20questions%20(where%20nothing%20could%20be%20submitted%20without%20an%20OTP%20which%20came%20to%20my%20mobile%20phone%3F)%20Why%20were%20these%20rules%20never%20given%20to%20MPs%20and%20if%20they%20were%2C%20why%20is%20every%20single%20MP%20sharing%20this%20ID%20an%20login%20with%20numerous%20people%3F%20Where%20was%20this%20Ethics%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20conscience%20when%20the%20government%20used%20the%20Israeli%20software%20Pegasus%20to%20spy%20on%20the%20judiciary%2C%20independent%20journalists%2C%20and%20members%20of%20the%20opposition%3F%20Was%20this%20not%20a%20grievous%20breach%20of%20national%20security%3F%E2%80%9D%20it%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoitra%20said%20that%20she%20was%20asked%20extremely%20personal%20questions%20about%20her%20private%20life.%20And%2C%20she%20added%2C%20this%20continued%20even%20after%20the%20chairman%20was%20warned%20by%20other%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20to%20refrain%20from%20asking%20such%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20hours%20of%20questioning%2C%20five%20of%20the%20committee%20members%20boycotted%20the%20proceedings%2C%20saying%20they%20would%20not%20be%20party%20to%20this%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Echeerharan%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9C%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98disrobing%20of%20a%20woman%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698933004000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02191244%2FF3JW4x7aAAAMxu-.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fparliamentary-ethics-committee-opposition-mps-mahua-moitra%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20member%20told%20The%20Wire%20that%20though%20the%20chairperson%20gave%20them%20a%20%E2%80%98confidential%E2%80%99%20report%20on%20the%20matter%2C%20some%20details%20were%20already%20released%20by%20the%20complainant%20Nishikant%20Dubey%20a%20day%20before.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fparliamentary-ethics-committee-opposition-mps-mahua-moitra%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple's%20Hacking%20Threat%20Message%3A%20CERT-In%20Starts%20Probe%2C%20Notice%20Sent%20to%20Tech%20Company%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F16102200%2F38162406612_fd4487d15b_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECERT-In%2C%20the%20nodal%20agency%20that%20deals%20with%20cybersecurity%20threats%2C%20has%20begun%20its%20investigation%20in%20the%20Apple%20threat%20notification%20issue%2C%20and%20a%20notice%20has%20been%20sent%20to%20the%20company%2C%20IT%20secretary%20S.%20Krishnan%20said%20on%20Thursday%20(November%202).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCERT-In%20has%20started%20its%20probe%E2%80%A6%20they%20(Apple)%20will%20cooperate%20in%20this%20probe%2C%E2%80%9D%20news%20agency%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India%20reported%20Krishnan%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fnotice-sent-to-apple-cert-in-has-started-probe-it-secretary-on-hacking-attempt-alert-issue%2Farticleshow%2F104907518.cms%5C%22%3Esaying%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20an%20event%20related%20to%20the%20MeitY-NSF%20research%20collaboration.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20threat%20relates%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fapple-india-state-sponsored-spyware%5C%22%3Emessage%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9CApple%20believes%20you%20are%20being%20targeted%20by%20state-sponsored%20attackers%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20remotely%20compromise%20the%20iPhone%20associated%20with%20your%20Apple%20ID%20%E2%80%A6.%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20was%20sent%20to%20by%20multiple%20opposition%20leaders%2C%20including%20Mahua%20Moitra%2C%20Raghav%20Chadha%2C%20and%20Shashi%20Tharoor.%20It%20was%20also%20sent%20to%20several%20journalists%2C%20including%20Siddharth%20Varadarajan%2C%20founding%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20Sriram%20Karri%2C%20resident%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Chronicle%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20and%20Ravi%20Nair%2C%20journalist%2C%20OCCRP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20email%20titled%20%E2%80%9CALERT%3A%20State-sponsored%20attackers%20may%20be%20targeting%20your%20iPhone%E2%80%9D%20goes%20on%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CThese%20attackers%20are%20likely%20targeting%20you%20individually%20because%20of%20who%20you%20are%20or%20what%20you%20do.%20If%20your%20device%20is%20compromised%20by%20a%20state-sponsored%20attacker%2C%20they%20may%20be%20able%20to%20remotely%20access%20your%20sensitive%20data%2C%20communications%2C%20or%20even%20the%20camera%20and%20microphone.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20urges%20the%20recipients%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20it%E2%80%99s%20possible%20this%20is%20a%20false%20alarm%2C%20please%20take%20this%20warning%20seriously.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20on%20October%2031%2C%20Apple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fapple-india-state-sponsored-spyware%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CApple%20does%20not%20attribute%20the%20threat%20notifications%20to%20any%20specific%20state-sponsored%20attacker.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20threat%20notifications%20were%20enabled%20by%20the%20company%20in%202021%2C%20and%20since%20then%20such%20notifications%20have%20reportedly%20been%20sent%20to%20individuals%20in%20nearly%20150%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFollowing%20opposition%20MPs%E2%80%99%20claims%20of%20receiving%20these%20hacking%20attempt%20warnings%2C%20IT%20Minister%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fgovt-orders-probe-after-opposition-mps-claims-of-receiving-hacking-attempt-warnings-from-apple%2Fcid%2F1976648%5C%22%3Eissued%20a%20statement%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20government%20takes%20its%20role%20of%20protecting%20the%20privacy%20and%20security%20of%20all%20citizens%20very%20seriously.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20notification%20about%20%E2%80%98state-sponsored%20attacks%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9Cseems%20vague%20and%20non-specific%20in%20nature%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20the%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Electronics%20and%20IT%20Rajeev%20Chandrasekhar%20had%20said%20that%20the%20government%20wants%20Apple%20to%20clarify%20if%20its%20devices%20are%20secure%20and%20why%20%E2%80%98threat%20notifications%E2%80%99%20were%20sent%20to%20people%20in%20over%20150%20countries%2C%20given%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20repeated%20claims%20about%20its%20products%20being%20designed%20for%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20names%20in%20the%20hacking%20attempt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fapple-india-state-sponsored-spyware%5C%22%3Elist%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20well-known%20people%20who%20are%20open%20critics%20of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20questions%20raised%20in%20this%20matter%20are%20a%20source%20of%20concern%2C%20as%20per%20many%20experts%2C%20who%20refocused%20attention%20on%20the%202021%20Pegasus%20Project%20that%20revealed%20that%20over%20a%20dozen%20phones%20in%20India%2C%20belonging%20to%20politicians%2C%20journalists%2C%20human%20rights%20activists%2C%20and%20others%2C%20were%20infected%20with%20Israeli%20spyware.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20members%20whose%20phones%20were%20infected%20with%20the%20spyware%20included%20then%20Congress%20president%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20lawyers%2C%20a%20sitting%20judge%2C%20an%20election%20commissioner%2C%20the%20ousted%20CBI%20director%20and%20family%20members%20of%20such%20persons%20also%2C%20just%20before%20and%20after%20the%20previous%20general%20elections%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court-appointed%20committee%20investigating%20this%20matter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fsupreme-court-pegasus-spyware-case-8110566%2F%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20did%20not%20cooperate%20with%20its%20investigation%2C%20while%20adding%20that%20it%20found%20no%20conclusive%20evidence%20of%20spyware%20use%20in%20the%20examined%20phones.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20had%20submitted%20its%20final%20report%20to%20the%20apex%20court%20in%20August%20last%20year.%20However%2C%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpegasus-committee-supreme-court-report-submitted%5C%22%3Eare%20yet%20to%20be%20made%20public%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20also%20did%20not%20explicitly%20deny%20that%20it%20uses%20Pegasus.%20With%20Apple%E2%80%99s%20not