-8840-7f28d05e4095.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESrinagar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Livelihood%20concerns%20have%20hit%20the%20villages%20along%20the%20International%20Border%20in%20Jammu%20after%20Pakistan%20violated%20the%20ceasefire%20last%20week%2C%20injuring%20two%20BSF%20troopers%20and%20a%20civilian.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20officials%2C%20Pakistani%20rangers%20fired%20at%20Indian%20posts%20on%20the%20night%20of%20October%2026%2C%20and%20some%20of%20the%20mortar%20shells%20landed%20in%20residential%20areas%20in%20Arnia%20and%20RS%20Pura%20sectors%2C%20some%2030%20km%20from%20the%20capital%20Jammu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20shelling%2C%20which%20continued%20until%20morning%20on%20October%2027%2C%20triggered%20panic%20among%20the%20villagers%20in%20the%20Arnia%20and%20RS%20Pura%20sectors%20along%20the%20International%20Border%2C%20forcing%20many%20of%20them%20to%20flee%20their%20residences.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELocated%20in%20Arnia%20tehsil%20of%20Jammu%20division%2C%20Trewa%2C%20which%20is%20predominantly%20an%20agricultural%20village%2C%20shares%20a%20nearly%20five-km%20border%20with%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOfficials%20said%20that%20some%20crops%20and%20at%20least%20five%20residential%20homes%20were%20damaged%20in%20the%20village%20due%20to%20the%20ceasefire%20violation%2C%20which%20was%20the%20second%20such%20incident%20in%2010%20days%20and%20the%20fifth%20since%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20entered%20into%20a%20fresh%20truce%20on%20February%2025%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2017%2C%20two%20BSF%20personnel%20were%20injured%20in%20unprovoked%20firing%20by%20Pakistani%20Rangers%20in%20the%20Arnia%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20border%20residents%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20have%20been%20living%20in%20peace%20since%20the%20two%20nuclear-armed%20countries%20revived%20their%202003%20ceasefire%20agreement.%20But%20the%20latest%20incidents%20have%20put%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20agreement%20in%20peril.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20anguished%20residents%20are%20cleaning%20up%20the%20underground%20bunkers%20that%20had%20fallen%20into%20disuse%20since%202021%20when%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Islamabad%20agreed%20to%20uphold%20the%20ceasefire%20agreement%2C%20basmati%20rice%20farmers%20are%20facing%20fear%20and%20uncertainty%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20harvest%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20shelling%20has%20revived%20the%20fears%20of%20an%20escalation%20in%20violence%20along%20the%20International%20Border%20in%20the%20coming%20days.%20Locals%20said%20that%20farmers%20are%20afraid%20of%20venturing%20into%20their%20paddy%20fields%20to%20harvest%20their%20crops%2C%20putting%20their%20livelihood%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHundreds%20of%20farmers%20are%20involved%20in%20basmati%20rice%20cultivation.%20They%20work%20day%20and%20night%20for%20six%20months.%20The%20shelling%20could%20not%20have%20come%20at%20a%20worse%20time%20for%20them%20as%20they%20are%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20harvest%20season%2C%E2%80%9D%20Balbir%20Kaur%2C%20sarpanch%20of%20Trewa%20village%20in%20Arnia%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20over%20the%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20the%20government%20will%20help%20the%20farmers%20in%20harvesting%20their%20crops%20without%20any%20delay%20by%20procuring%20more%20manpower%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20cover%2050%25%20of%20the%20harvest%20cost%20as%20a%20goodwill%20gesture%20for%20alleviating%20the%20suffering%20of%20farmers%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kaur%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02171649%2F1e69c4de-fdc3-4862-aa3f-180c7f75ffcc.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02171649%2F1e69c4de-fdc3-4862-aa3f-180c7f75ffcc.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02171649%2F1e69c4de-fdc3-4862-aa3f-180c7f75ffcc-300x163.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02171649%2F1e69c4de-fdc3-4862-aa3f-180c7f75ffcc-1024x556.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683196%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22652%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESarpanch%20Balbir%20Kaur%20interacting%20with%20locals%20after%20the%20recent%20ceasefire%20violation%20which%20damaged%20five%20residential%20homes%20in%20Trewa%20village.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20reports%2C%20locals%20in%20Arnia%20have%20already%20started%20preparations%20for%20more%20difficult%20times%20amid%20the%20ongoing%20political%20uncertainty%20across%20the%20border%20following%20the%20ouster%20of%20Imran%20Khan%20as%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20unprovoked%20firing%20last%20week%2C%20residents%20of%20Trewa%20and%20adjoining%20villages%20in%20Arnia%20and%20RS%20Pura%20have%20cleaned%20up%20dozens%20of%20underground%20bunkers%20built%20by%20the%20government%2C%20where%20they%20take%20refuge%20when%20the%20situation%20heats%20up%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20administration%20in%20Jammu%20has%20also%20banned%20the%20sale%20and%20use%20of%20firecrackers%20during%20marriage%20ceremonies%20and%20other%20celebrations%20to%20prevent%20any%20confusion%20or%20rumour-mongering%20amid%20the%20simmering%20border%20tensions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPakistan%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20trusted.%20If%20they%20do%20it%20(mortar%20shelling)%20once%2C%20they%20will%20do%20it%20again.%20For%20me%2C%20the%20immediate%20priority%20is%20to%20help%20the%20farmers%20in%20harvesting%20their%20crops.%20Besides%2C%20we%20are%20also%20holding%20regular%20meetings%20with%20the%20residents%20so%20that%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20feel%20ignored%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kaur%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Kisan%20Advisory%20Board.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20a%20patrol%20party%20of%20Border%20Security%20Forces%20detected%20and%20defused%20an%20unexploded%20mortar%20shell%20which%20was%20fired%20by%20Pakistan%20Rangers%20on%20October%2026.%20The%20BSF%20has%20already%20lodged%20a%20protest%20with%20Pakistan%20Rangers%20over%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20farms%20and%20houses%20are%20not%20safe%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20flag%20meeting%20between%20the%20armies%20(of%20India%20and%20Pakistan).%20Once%20it%20happens%2C%20there%20will%20be%20some%20hope%20that%20the%20situation%20will%20calm%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20local%20who%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20named%20over%20the%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20situation%20has%20calmed%20down%20and%20no%20fresh%20incident%20of%20firing%20was%20reported%20after%20last%20week%E2%80%99s%20ceasefire%20violation%2C%20residents%20are%20not%20leaving%20anything%20up%20to%20fate.%20%E2%80%9CAn%20evacuation%20plan%20has%20been%20prepared.%20In%2030%20minutes%2C%20all%20the%20residents%20will%20be%20in%20underground%20bunkers%20if%20something%20ugly%20happens%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kaur%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20Pakistan%20used%20mortar%20shells%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20two%20years%2C%20authorities%20have%20put%20the%20BSF%20on%20a%20high%20alert%20along%20the%20International%20Border%20in%20Jammu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20BSF%20continues%20to%20monitor%20the%20developments%20closely%2C%20while%20assessing%20the%20situation%20and%20remains%20alert%20to%20respond%20as%20necessary%20to%20ensure%20the%20safety%20and%20security%20of%20the%20border%20and%20its%20residents%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20BSF%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20shares%20a%203%2C323-km%20border%20with%20Pakistan%2C%20including%20965%20km%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20While%20221%20km%20is%20the%20demarcated%20International%20Border%2C%20744%20km%20is%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20which%20came%20up%20as%20a%20result%20of%20hostilities%20between%20the%20two%20South%20Asian%20neighbours%20after%20the%201947%20partition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20sanctioned%20the%20construction%20of%2018%2C460%20individual%20and%20community%20bunkers%20in%20five%20districts%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20%E2%80%93%20Jammu%2C%20Kathua%2C%20Samba%2C%20Poonch%2C%20and%20Rajouri%20which%20fall%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20and%20International%20Border%20to%20shield%20border%20residents%20from%20Pakistani%20shelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698928167000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02171714%2F6b5c8022-678b-4bd2-8840-7f28d05e4095.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpakistan-violates-ceasefire-residents-border-villages-fear-uncertainty%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20shelling%20has%20revived%20the%20fears%20of%20an%20escalation%20in%20violence%20along%20the%20International%20Border%20in%20the%20coming%20days.%20Locals%20said%20that%20farmers%20are%20afraid%20of%20venturing%20into%20their%20paddy%20fields%20to%20harvest%20their%20crops%2C%20putting%20their%20livelihood%20at%20risk.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpakistan-violates-ceasefire-residents-border-villages-fear-uncertainty%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Can%20the%20Modi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Schemes%20Bring%20About%20Transformative%20Change%20in%20Rural%20Livelihoods%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F02213735%2FTap-water.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20in%20a%20two-part%20explainer%20by%20the%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNES%20InfoSphere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20team%20from%20its%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2F_files%2Fugd%2F85c814_77f033eb2fb1422a94e9cabdd59f0bde.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Elatest%20edition%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20as%20part%20of%20its%20special%20research%20series%20on%20Arthvyavastha%3A%20Measuring%20the%20State%20of%20the%20Indian%20Economy.%20To%20review%20InfoSphere%E2%80%99s%20research%20work%2C%20please%20view%20its%20website%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20part%20of%20this%20series%20helped%20explain%20the%20nature%20of%20concerns%20affecting%20India%E2%80%99s%20macro%20and%20micro%20rural%20performance%20indicators%20from%20a%20lower%20disbursement%20and%20budgeted%20ratio%20of%20fiscal%20priorities%20weighted%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20during%20its%20elected%20term.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20lower%20fiscal%20outlay%20and%20disproportionate%20rate%20of%20disbursement%20for%20schemes%20applicable%20have%20contributed%20directly%20to%20the%20poorer%20functioning%20of%20certain%20schemes%2C%20including%20those%20like%20MGNREGA%20which%20have%20been%20around%20for%20long%20and%20have%20been%20instrumental%20in%20providing%20some%20job%20security%20for%20an%20otherwise%20underemployed%20rural%20population%20across%20states.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20look%20here%20at%20the%20performance%20of%20some%20more%20schemes%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%20and%20the%20factors%20that%20play%20a%20role%20in%20contributing%20to%20developmental%20prospects.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPradhan%20Mantri%20Kisan%20Samman%20Nidhi%20(PM-KISAN)%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPM-KISAN%20Yojana%20aims%20to%20supplement%20the%20financial%20needs%20of%20the%20farmers%20in%20acquiring%20various%20inputs%20to%20ensure%20proper%20crop%20health%20and%20appropriate%20yields%20and%20generate%20equivalent%20expected%20income%20for%20the%20farmers.%20This%20nationwide%20scheme%20was%20announced%20in%20the%202019%20interim%20budget%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20small%20and%20marginal%20farmers%20would%20receive%20Rs%206%2C000%20per%20year%20in%20three%20payments%2C%20which%20will%20be%20put%20directly%20into%20their%20bank%20accounts%20under%20this%20initiative.%20The%20Union%20government%20would%20fund%20the%20total%20yearly%20expenditure%20for%20this%20initiative.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20programme%E2%80%99s%20benefits%20are%20now%20available%20to%20all%20farmers%20nationwide%20without%20the%20need%20for%20intermediaries%20through%20a%20farmer-centric%20digital%20infrastructure%20that%20upholds%20complete%20transparency%20in%20beneficiary%20verification%20and%20registration.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20of%20August%202023%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20has%20disbursed%20over%20Rs%202.60%20lakhs%20crores%20to%20more%20than%2011%20crore%20farmers.%20In%20the%20last%20financial%20year%20i.e.%202022-23%2C%20a%20total%20amount%20of%20Rs%2058%2C201.85%20crore%20was%20disbursed%20to%20eligible%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02155643%2Fimage1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22752%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02155643%2Fimage1.png%20752w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02155643%2Fimage1-300x180.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683175%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22452%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBeneficiaries%20of%20the%20scheme.%20Source%3A%20Infosphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20above%20graph%20depicts%20a%20substantial%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20farmers%20receiving%20benefits%20from%20the%20programme.%20Since%20its%20inception%20in%202019%2C%20the%20number%20of%20beneficiaries%20has%20increased%20dramatically%2C%20from%203%20billion%20to%2030%20billion%20by%202021.%20Notably%2C%20data%20for%20the%202022-23%20fiscal%20year%20were%20only%20available%20through%20November%202022%2C%20which%20may%20explain%20the%20lower%20beneficiary%20count%20for%20the%202022-23%20fiscal%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20main%20concern%20for%20the%20scheme%20is%20the%20underutilisation%20of%20the%20allocated%20funds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02155848%2Fimage2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22752%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02155848%2Fimage2.png%20752w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02155848%2Fimage2-300x180.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683176%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22451%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBudget%20Estimate%20vs%20Amount%20Released.%20Source%3A%20Infosphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20above%20graph%20demonstrates%20conclusively%20that%20the%20government%20has%20consistently%20underutilised%20the%20allocated%20funds%20for%20the%20programme.%20Except%20for%202021%2C%20the%20government%20consistently%20underutilised%20the%20allocated%20funds.%20A%20budget%20overrun%20in%202021%20was%20primarily%20attributable%20to%20the%20necessity%20of%20meeting%20the%20requirements%20of%20farmers%20during%20the%20second%20wave%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02160050%2Fimage3-1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22901%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02160050%2Fimage3-1.png%20901w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02160050%2Fimage3-1-300x188.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683177%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22564%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPercentage%20Budget%20Under-Utilisation.%20Source%3A%20Infosphere%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20above%20chart%20shows%20that%20the%20government%20made%20efforts%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20underutilisation%20but%20still%20confronts%20an%20average%20rate%20of%2024%25%20of%20the%20budgeted%20amount.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFactors%20shaping%20rural%20development%20patterns%20across%20India%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFirstly%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20literacy%20rate%20trends%20have%20a%20major%20impact%20on%20rural%20development%20scenarios.%20A%20higher%20literacy%20rate%2C%20especially%20amongst%20girls%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20has%20been%20responsible%20for%20the%20improved%20performance%20of%20many%20public%20health%20statistics%20and%20over%20time%20helped%20rural%20youth%20get%20absorbed%20in%20higher-paying%2C%20and%20better-condition%20employment%20opportunities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmospi.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpublication_reports%2FReport_585_75th_round_Education_final_1507_0.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENSS%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ereports%2C%20the%20literacy%20rate%20in%20rural%20India%20increased%20from%2068%25%20for%20males%20and%2043%25%20for%20females%20in%202000%20to%2072.3%25%20for%20males%20and%2056.8%25%20for%20females%20in%202014.%20Between%202003%20and%202014%2C%20rural%20literacy%20grew%20at%20a%20compound%20annual%20growth%20rate%20(CAGR)%20of%20approximately%203.42%25.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ibef.org%2Fblogs%2Frural-education-integral-to-india-s-progress%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cspan%3E%20the%20literacy%20rate%20stood%20at%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Earound%2073.5%25%20in%20rural%20India%2C%20including%2081%25%20for%20males%20and%2065%25%20for%20females.%20The%20government%20of%20India%20has%20launched%20many%20initiatives%20such%20as%20Samagra%20Shiksha%2C%20Jahawar%20Navodaya%20Vidyalaya%2C%20mid-day%20meal%20schemes%2C%20etc.%20to%20increase%20the%20enrolment%20rate%20and%20also%20to%20encourage%20the%20already%20enrolled%20students%20to%20attend%20regularly%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20rise%20in%20literacy%20rates.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStill%2C%20rural%20India%20requires%20a%20strong%20infrastructure%2C%20including%20roads%2C%20communication%20channels%2C%20electricity%2C%20drinking%20water%2C%20irrigation%2C%20drainage%2C%20and%20adequate%20housing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcensusindia.gov.in%2Fcensus.website%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECensus%202011%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%2045%25%20of%20rural%20households%20do%20not%20have%20electricity%20connections%20and%20depend%20on%20kerosene%20and%20other%20means%20for%20lighting%20and%20merely%2030%25%20of%20rural%20areas%20are%20covered%20with%20tap%20water%20supply.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20sanitation%20facilities%20in%20rural%20areas%20are%20also%20not%20adequate.%20As%20per%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmorth.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FBasic_Road_Statistics_of_India_2012_13_0.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eroad%20statistics%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20published%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20for%202012-13%2C%20rural%20roads%20span%2060.39%20km%20of%20every%20100%20km.%20Further%2C%20the%20rural%20surfaced%20road%20is%20just%2033%25%20of%20the%20total%20rural%20road%20network%20in%20India%20and%20the%20remaining%20are%20kutcha%20roads%20which%20are%20highly%20vulnerable%20and%20inaccessible%2C%20particularly%20during%20the%20rainy%20season.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVarious%20schemes%20and%20initiatives%20are%20being%20undertaken%20by%20the%20current%20government%20including%20the%20Jal%20Jeevan%20Mission%20which%20aims%20to%20provide%20functional%20household%20tap%20connection%20to%20every%20rural%20household%20by%202024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20As%20of%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investindia.gov.in%2Fteam-india-blogs%2Frural-infrastructure-sector-under-national-infrastructure-pipeline%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDecember%2031%2C%202019%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20road%20length%20worth%20Rs.%202.9%20lakh%20crore%20had%20been%20sanctioned%20and%20expenditure%20of%20Rs.%202.17%20lakh%20crore%20was%20incurred.%20The%20vision%20for%202025%20is%20for%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investindia.gov.in%2Fteam-india-blogs%2Frural-infrastructure-sector-under-national-infrastructure-pipeline%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E100%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20rural%20population%20to%20have%20access%20to%20pucca%20houses%20with%20basic%20civic%20amenities%20such%20as%20piped%20drinking%20water%2C%20power%20supply%20and%20LPG%20connections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGovernment%20policies%20have%20helped%20to%20develop%20rural%20India%2C%20creating%20new%20job%20opportunities.%20One%20such%20initiative%20is%20TRYSEM%2C%20or%20Training%20Rural%20Youth%20for%20Self-Employment.%20It%20aims%20to%20train%20young%20people%20in%20technical%20skills%20so%20that%20they%20can%20start%20their%20businesses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMulti-pronged%20strategies%20are%20being%20taken%20by%20the%20Government%20to%20address%20issues%20relating%20to%20employment%20opportunities%20through%20centrally%20sponsored%20schemes%20like%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fharyanarural.gov.in%2Fmahatma-gandhi-national-rural-employment-guarantee-scheme-mgnregs%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Government%2520of%2520India%2520passed%2Cto%2520do%2520unskilled%2520manual%2520work.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMGNREGS%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.myscheme.gov.in%2Fschemes%2Fday-nrlm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDeendayal%2520Antyodaya%2520Yojana%2520%252D%2520National%2520Rural%2520Livelihoods%2520Mission%2520(DAY%252DNRLM%2Ca%2520range%2520of%2520financial%2520services%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EDeendayal%20Antyoday%20Yojana-%20National%20Rural%20Livelihood%20Mission%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frural.nic.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FRTI_DDUGKY_05112021.pdf%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EDeendayal%20Upadhyay-%20Gramin%20Kaushalya%20Yojana%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fomms.nic.in%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EPradhan%20Mantri%20Gram%20Sadak%20Yojana%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20launched%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1796217%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGarib%20Kalyan%20Rojgar%20Abhiyaan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3E(GKRA)%20of%20125%20days%20on%20June%2020%2C%202020%20to%20boost%20employment%20and%20livelihood%20opportunities%20for%20returnee%20migrant%20workers%20and%20similarly%20affected%20persons%20including%20youth%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20in%20116%20selected%20districts%20across%20Bihar%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Odisha%2C%20Rajasthan%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20The%20Abhiyaan%20has%20achieved%20an%20employment%20generation%20of%2050.78%20crore%20person-days%20with%20a%20total%20expenditure%20of%20Rs%2039%2C293%20crore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rise%20of%20mass%20media%2C%20such%20as%20television%2C%20social%20media%2C%20and%20radio%2C%20has%20increased%20awareness%20among%20rural%20people.%20With%20mobile%20phones%20and%20the%20Internet%2C%20they%20can%20now%20search%20for%20jobs%2C%20learn%20new%20skills%2C%20and%20connect%20with%20people%20outside%20of%20their%20village.%20This%20has%20also%20made%20them%20more%20aware%20of%20different%20government%20schemes%20that%20can%20help%20them%20with%20farming%20and%20other%20activities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ficar.org.in%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20Council%20of%20Agricultural%20Research%20(ICAR)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20%3Cspan%3Eis%20responsible%20for%20agricultural%20research%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20helps%20understand%20how%20crop%20yields%20are%20affected%20by%20different%20atmospheric%20and%20soil%20conditions%2C%20and%20how%20fertilizers%20can%20be%20used%20to%20increase%20production%20leading%20to%20the%20overall%20development%20of%20the%20rural%20areas.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ficar.org.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-07%2FSignificant%2520Achievements%2520During%25202014-23%2520English%252017%2520July%252023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2014%20to%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cspan%3E%20ICAR%20has%20been%20able%20to%20release%202%2C764%20varieties%20of%20field%20and%20horticultural%20crops%20including%20123%20bio-fortified%20varieties.%20It%20has%20enhanced%20export-oriented%20production%20of%20horticultural%20crops%20and%20gene%20modifications%20to%20explore%20improved%20resistance%20to%20biotic%2Fabiotic%20stresses.%20ICAR%20was%20able%20to%20develop%2028%20eco-friendly%20pest%20management%20modules%20and.%2053%20multi-enterprise%20integrated%20farming%20systems%20(IFS).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIn%20summation%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20root%20is%20still%20habituated%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20its%20villages%20even%20though%2C%20paradoxically%2C%20its%20cities%20power%20the%20growth%20story.%20The%20appropriation%20of%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Findicators%2Fbright-spot-rural-consumption-to-pick-up-on-wage-rise-and-lower-inflation-say-economists%2Farticleshow%2F101647375.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erural%20populations%E2%80%99%20hard%20work%20has%20become%20a%20cost-benefit%20advantage%20for%20urban%20areas%20to%20source%20cheap%20migrant%20worker%20bases%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20One%20can%20see%20that%20while%20analysing%20the%20growth%20of%20construction%2C%20or%20MSMEs%20too.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUpon%20assuming%20office%20in%202014%2C%20the%20Modi%20administration%20instilled%20considerable%20optimism%20on%20the%20prospects%20of%20rural%20reform%20and%20the%20lofty%20objective%20of%20doubling%20the%20earnings%20of%20farmers.%20Nevertheless%2C%20in%202019%2C%20the%20development%20achieved%20was%20not%20in%20line%20with%20the%20initial%20expectations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20a%20considerable%20segment%20of%20the%20rural%20voting%20population%20maintained%20a%20sense%20of%20optimism%20and%20adopted%20a%20cautious%20stance%2C%20expecting%20that%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20subsequent%20term%20in%20office%20would%20yield%20the%20desired%20transformations%20they%20longed%20for.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F26171336%2Fdap.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F26171336%2Fdap.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F26171336%2Fdap-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F26171336%2Fdap-1024x513.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F26171336%2Fdap-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-530667%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22601%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20a%20farmer%20spraying%20fertilizer.%20Photo%3A%20IFPRI%2FFlickr%20CC%20BY%20NC%20ND%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERoad%20construction%20and%20better%20connectivity%20have%20helped%20remote%20areas%20to%20be%20better%20connected%20than%20before%20but%20rural%20livelihoods%2C%20and%20access%20to%20basic%20amenities%2C%20including%20better%20education%2C%20healthcare%2C%20or%20employment%2C%20remain%20a%20distant%20goal.%20This%20has%20negatively%20impacted%20the%20upward%20mobility%20promise%20that%20(new)%20governments%20bring%20with%20them%20when%20they%20expect%20to%20be%20voted%20back%20to%20power.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EProgrammes%20like%20MGNREGS%20have%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frural.nic.in%2Fen%2Fpress-release%2Fstudy-assess-impact-mgnregs%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMahatma%2520Gandhi%2520NREGS%2520has%2520had%2Cin%2520wages%2520of%2520rural%2520workers%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebrought%20a%20tangible%20difference%20to%20the%20rural%20economy%20and%20contributed%20to%20its%20growth%20rates%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20but%20require%20more%20funding%20and%20expansion.%20What%20has%20been%20observed%20is%20a%20reverse%20effect%20in%20the%20support%20for%20these%20%E2%80%93%20and%20more%20centrally%20budgeted%20schemes%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20second%20term.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFiscal%20insecurities%20are%20driving%20this%2C%20but%20a%20lack%20of%20intent%20and%20will%20to%20bring%20a%20transformative%2C%20long-term%20change%20in%20rural%20livelihoods%20will%20not%20only%20affect%20the%20aspirational%20hopes%20of%20the%20current%20generation%20but%20also%20the%20future%20ones.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20director%2C%20CNES.%20Amisha%20Singh%20and%20Aditi%20Desai%20are%20research%20assistants%20with%20CNES%20and%20co-leads%20of%20the%20InfoSphere%20team.%20Vasudevan%2C%20Shilpa%20Santhosh%2C%20Aryan%20Govindakrishnan%20and%20Jheel%20Doshi%20are%20members%20of%20the%20InfoSphere%20team%20and%20research%20assistants%20with%20CNES.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698926425000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F02213735%2FTap-water.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcan-the-modi-governments-schemes-bring-about-transformative-change-in-rural-livelihoods%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Analysing%20the%20performance%20of%20some%20schemes%20by%20government%20and%20the%20factors%20that%20play%20a%20role%20in%20contributing%20to%20developmental%20prospects.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcan-the-modi-governments-schemes-bring-about-transformative-change-in-rural-livelihoods%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI%20Summit%20in%20UK%20Seeks%20Global%20Consensus%20on%20Mitigating%20Risk%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02120652%2FAI-Safety-Summit-1-e1698907074576.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3