Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWithin%20this%20familiar%20mould%20of%20a%20thriller%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKaala%20Paani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20stands%20out%20because%20it%20stays%20true%20to%20the%20tragedy%20of%20an%20epidemic%20that%20engulfs%20the%20characters%20rather%20than%20focusing%20on%20a%20protagonist%20heroically%20finding%20a%20cure%20for%20the%20disease.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F6ph4WPZIrbM%3Fsi%3D8MQBvkM_It3wCuA1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20pilot%20episode%20of%20the%20show%2C%20multiple%20characters%20are%20introduced%20whose%20reaction%20to%20the%20quarantine%20is%20largely%20informed%20by%20their%20past%20trauma.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr%20Soudamini%20Singh%2C%20brilliantly%20portrayed%20by%20Mona%20Singh%2C%20follows%20a%20pattern%20of%20symptoms%20in%20her%20patients%20that%20leads%20her%20to%20believe%20there%20is%20an%20unknown%20and%20deadly%20disease%20present%20on%20the%20islands.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20all%20her%20attempts%20to%20alert%20the%20authorities%20are%20quashed%20in%20favour%20of%20hosting%20a%20corporate-sponsored%20festival%20that%20would%20bring%20millions%20of%20tourists%20to%20the%20island.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20episode%2C%20she%20finally%20figures%20out%20the%20source%20of%20the%20infected%20water%20that%20led%20to%20the%20epidemic%20but%20loses%20her%20life%20as%20she%20tries%20to%20prevent%20its%20circulation.%20With%20her%20death%2C%20the%20crisis%20intensifies%2C%20and%20the%20storyline%20deftly%20moves%20away%20from%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20heroic%20resolution%20to%20the%20communal%20crisis%20of%20the%20epidemic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20show%E2%80%99s%20meticulous%20investment%20in%20each%20of%20the%20characters%E2%80%99%20past%20often%20sometimes%20makes%20the%20storyline%20feel%20stagnant.%20However%2C%20despite%20the%20occasional%20lag%20in%20plot%20progression%2C%20the%20fast-paced%20nature%20of%20the%20show%20makes%20up%20for%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr%20Gagra%2C%20a%20researcher%20played%20by%20Radhika%20Mehrotra%2C%20is%20another%20pivotal%20character%20in%20determining%20the%20course%20of%20the%20epidemic%20crisis.%20Although%20a%20competent%20and%20experienced%20scholar%2C%20her%20self-doubt%20and%20trauma%20about%20her%20caste%20identity%20often%20hinder%20her%20journey%20towards%20finding%20the%20cure.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EL.G.%20Qadri%2C%20played%20by%20Ashutosh%20Gowariker%2C%20in%20a%20theatrical%20speech%20introduces%20%E2%80%98the%20trolley%20problem%E2%80%99%20upon%20which%20the%20moral%20dilemma%20of%20the%20show%20hinges.%20This%20philosophical%20experiment%20asks%3A%20if%20one%20had%20a%20choice%2C%20should%20they%20allow%20a%20train%20to%20run%20on%20its%20track%20and%20kill%20five%20people%20working%20ahead%2C%20or%20should%20they%20flip%20the%20switch%20so%20that%20the%20train%20changes%20its%20track%20and%20kills%20one%20innocent%20person%20instead%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkaala-paani-is-a-well-mounted-thriller-that-doesnt-trust-itself-enough-to-forgo-the-melodrama%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Kaala%20Paani%E2%80%99%20Is%20a%20Well%20Mounted%20Thriller%20That%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20Trust%20Itself%20Enough%20To%20Forgo%20the%20Melodrama%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20becomes%20the%20potent%20tool%20with%20which%20every%20cruel%20bureaucratic%20choice%20is%20justified%2C%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20even%20the%20genocide%20of%20tribal%20communities%20is%20proposed%20and%20considered%20as%20the%20difficult%20but%20righteous%20option%20towards%20the%20climax%20of%20the%20show.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20a%20local%20taxi%20driver%20named%20Chiranjeevi%20(played%20by%20Sukant%20Goel)%20who%20was%20a%20sceptic%20of%20tribal%20welfare%20activism%20and%20the%20environment%2C%20finally%20becomes%20a%20devoted%20protector%20of%20the%20tribal%20community%20after%20discovering%20a%20deeper%20connection.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20show%20also%20features%20a%20corrupt%20police%20officer%2C%20played%20with%20mirth%20and%20humour%20by%20Amey%20Wagh%2C%20who%20colludes%20with%20corporate%20overlords%20to%20escape%20the%20islands.%20Throughout%20the%20series%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20corporation%20points%20towards%20a%20sinister%20cause%20behind%20the%20disease%2C%20but%20it%20remains%20a%20cliffhanger%20till%20the%20very%20end.%20As%20the%20characters%20develop%20throughout%20the%20show%2C%20their%20concerns%20and%20interests%20also%20change%20and%20influence%20the%20final%20outcome.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20makers%20of%20the%20show%20also%20refrain%20from%20assuming%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20tribal%20community%20while%20trying%20to%20make%20them%20play%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20determining%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20island.%20However%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20characterisation%20just%20to%20avoid%20appropriation%20feels%20too%20cautious%20and%20unsatisfactory%20at%20times.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20show%20does%20not%20relent%20to%20the%20traditional%20structure%20of%20valorising%20and%20celebrating%20certain%20protagonists%20as%20being%20the%20saviours%20while%20sidelining%20loss%20and%20suffering.%20Rather%2C%20it%20uses%20the%20crisis%20caused%20by%20an%20epidemic%20to%20draw%20parallels%20with%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20the%20characters%E2%80%99%20actions%20and%20not%20the%20characters%20themselves%20that%20serve%20as%20the%20antagonists%20and%20protagonists%20of%20the%20show.%20The%20show%20builds%20up%20an%20emotional%20trajectory%20in%20each%20of%20its%20characters%E2%80%99%20storylines%20that%20moves%20the%20audience%20and%20demands%20a%20few%20teary%20eyes%20quite%20often.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKaala%20Paani%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Estays%20committed%20to%20depicting%20human%20tragedy%20and%20even%20though%20season%20one%20ends%20with%20the%20promise%20of%20a%20cure%2C%20the%20cathartic%20release%20of%20a%20tragedy%20is%20what%20the%20audience%20carries%20with%20them%20and%20finds%20comfort%20in%20through%20a%20collective%20act%20of%20remembering%20the%20trauma%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDebabratee%20Dhar%20is%20an%20intern%20at%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698924560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02161000%2FKaala-Paani-featured-photo.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkaala-paani-review-tragedy-that-sacrifices-heroes-to-spotlight-errors-of-human-actions%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Netflix%20series%20stands%20out%20because%20it%20stays%20true%20to%20the%20tragedy%20of%20an%20epidemic%20that%20engulfs%20the%20characters%2C%20rather%20than%20focusing%20on%20a%20protagonist%20to%20heroically%20find%20a%20cure%20for%20the%20disease.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkaala-paani-review-tragedy-that-sacrifices-heroes-to-spotlight-errors-of-human-actions%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98An%20Urgent%20Intervention%E2%80%99%3A%20Poets%2C%20Scholars%20Discuss%20the%20Importance%20of%20Speaking%20Out%20On%20Palestine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02155254%2FIMG_5817.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Columbia%20University%20professor%20Rashid%20Khalidi%20and%20celebrated%20author%20Ta-Nehisi%20Coates%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20conversed%20about%20the%20history%20of%20Palestine%2C%20its%20resistance%20and%20the%20political%20realities%20of%20the%20United%20States%20in%20an%20event%20held%20in%20Jane%E2%80%99s%20Chapel%20in%20Manhattan%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20November%201%2C%20urging%20people%20watching%20to%20speak%20out%20against%20the%20war%20on%20Palestine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20free%20event%2C%20garnering%20about%203%2C000%20viewers%20both%20in%20person%20and%20online%2C%20was%20organised%20by%20the%20Palestine%20Festival%20of%20Literature%20and%20titled%20%E2%80%98But%20We%20Must%20Speak%3A%20On%20Palestine%20and%20the%20Mandates%20of%20Conscience.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYasmin%20El-Rifae%20addressed%20the%20audience%20as%20the%20producer%20of%20the%20Palestine%20Literary%20Festival%2C%20which%20has%20brought%20writers%20and%20artists%20from%20around%20the%20world%20to%20Palestine%20since%202008.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20of%20the%20writers%20and%20activists%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20whose%20homes%20PalFest%20visited%20just%20last%20May%20and%20in%20years%20prior%20are%20having%20their%20photographs%20and%20addresses%20circulated%20on%20chat%20groups%20among%20armed%20Israeli%20settlers%20calling%20for%20their%20murder.%E2%80%9D%20El-Rifae%20said.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20In%20response%20to%20this%20disaster%2C%20we%20are%20holding%20this%20event%20as%20an%20urgent%20intervention%20by%20writers%2C%20scholars%20and%20poets%20who%20have%20worked%20at%20the%20unavoidable%20intersection%20of%20art%20and%20politics%20%E2%80%94%20who%20have%20thought%20deeply%20about%20land%2C%20segregation%2C%20colonisation%2C%20history%20and%20liberation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECivil%20rights%20lawyer%20and%20author%20Michelle%20Alexander%20introduced%20the%20evening%2C%20acknowledging%20that%20in%201967%2C%20Dr.%20Martin%20Luther%20King%20Jr.%20was%20scheduled%20to%20give%20his%20speech%20condemning%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20in%20Jane%E2%80%99s%20Chapel%20as%20well.%20The%20speech%20was%20ultimately%20relocated%20to%20Riverside%20Church%2C%20but%20the%20parallels%20remained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlexander%20quoted%20from%20King%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20come%20to%20this%20magnificent%20house%20of%20worship%20tonight%20because%20my%20conscience%20leaves%20me%20no%20other%20choice.%20A%20time%20comes%20when%20silence%20is%20betrayal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKing%E2%80%99s%20speech%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20the%20event%E2%80%99s%20theme%20of%20breaking%20silence%20for%20the%20aim%20of%20liberation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20conversation%20moderated%20by%20Alexander%2C%20Khalidi%2C%20professor%20at%20Columbia%20University%20and%20Palestinian-American%20historian%20spoke%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20understanding%20the%20history%20of%20Palestine%20in%20order%20to%20understand%20its%20resistance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20part%20of%20a%20100-years%20war%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eon%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Palestine%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20war%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Palestine%2C%E2%80%9D%20Khalidi%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20war%20to%20implant%20a%20settler-colonial%20presence%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20an%20indigenous%20people%20which%20is%20being%20pushed%20out%20slowly%20but%20surely.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKhalidi%20was%20joined%20in%20this%20conversation%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerican%20author%20and%20journalist%20Ta-Nehisi%20Coates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fpalestine-israel-zionism-hindutva%5C%22%3EA%20Prayer%2C%20Chant%20and%20Protest%20Song%3A%20Faith%20Communities%20Must%20Resist%20Their%20Extremists%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECoates%20reflected%20on%20his%20time%20visiting%20Palestine%2C%20where%20he%20said%20he%20felt%20tremendous%20shame%20for%20not%20knowing%20how%20segregated%20the%20land%20was.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20can%20think%20back%20to%20all%20of%20the%20articles%20I%E2%80%99ve%20read%2C%20all%20the%20things%20I%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20said%20about%20how%20complicated%20and%20complex%20the%20situation%20is%20and%20the%20occupation%20is%2C%E2%80%9D%20Coates%20said.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%98It%E2%80%99s%20complex%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20complicated.%E2%80%99%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20made%20to%20sound%20as%20if%20you%20need%20a%20degree%20in%20Middle%20Eastern%20studies%20or%20some%20such%2C%20a%20PhD%2C%20to%20really%20understand%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening.%20But%20I%20understood%20the%20first%20day.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20him%2C%20he%20said%20speaking%20up%20is%20personal%20and%20he%20has%20debts%20to%20pay.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20think%20about%20how%20gracious%20people%20were%20when%20I%20was%20over%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20Coates%20said.%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20about%20how%20they%20took%20me%20into%20their%20homes%2C%20I%20think%20about%20how%20they%20fed%20me%2C%20and%20I%20think%20about%20how%20their%20only%20request%20was%3A%20%E2%80%98When%20you%20go%20back%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20lose%20your%20voice.%E2%80%99%20That%20was%20all%20they%20asked.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlexander%20shifted%20the%20conversation%20to%20the%20political%20realities%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20its%20unshakeable%20support%20for%20Israel%2C%20citing%20a%20speech%20delivered%20by%20Joe%20Biden%20in%201986%20where%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20look%20at%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%20time%20we%20stop%20apologising%20for%20our%20support%20for%20Israel.%20There%E2%80%99s%20no%20apology%20to%20be%20made.%20None.%20It%20is%20the%20best%20%243%20billion%20dollar%20investment%20we%20make.%E2%80%9D%20She%20asked%20Khalidi%20and%20Coates%20what%20people%20needed%20to%20understand%20about%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20statement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKhalidi%20said%20that%20in%20addition%20to%20political%20strategy%20and%20imperial%20interests%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20understand%20that%20politicians%20are%20%E2%80%9Cbought%20and%20sold%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20like%20politicians%2C%20university%20administrations%20and%20the%20media%20kowtow%20to%20a%20single%20narrative%20because%20of%20money%20and%20power.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20not%20a%20war%20on%20the%20Palestinians%20waged%20by%20the%20Zionist%20movement%20or%20Israel%20alone.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20war%20waged%20on%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20by%20Israel%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%E2%80%9D%20Khalidi%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThose%20are%20our%20weapons.%20Those%20are%20American%20F-35s%2C%20American%20F-15s.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20to%20do%20something%20about%20our%20complicity%20in%20the%20killing%20so%20far%20of%209%2C000%20people%2C%20almost%204%2C000%20of%20them%20children.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECoates%20closed%20off%20the%20conversation%20speaking%20of%20his%20responsibility%20and%20moral%20conscience.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20midst%20of%20bombs%20being%20dropped%20on%20children%2C%20you%20have%20to%20speak%2C%E2%80%9D%20Coates%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20conversation%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20message%20from%20Rabbis%20Brant%20Rosen%20and%20Alissa%20Wise%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwo