nth-low-11698863671078.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20the%20October%20PMI%20Manufacturing%20data%20was%20above%20its%20long-run%20average%20of%2053.9%2C%20it%20was%20the%20slowest%20rate%20of%20expansion%20recorded%20since%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPMI%20values%20are%20reported%20as%20a%20single%20number%20(usually%20on%20a%20scale%20of%200-100)%2C%20where%20values%20above%2050%20typically%20indicate%20expansion%2C%20and%20values%20below%2050%20suggest%20contraction.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20rate%20of%20job%20creation%20was%20the%20slowest%20since%20April%2C%20the%20survey%20noted%2C%20adding%20that%20only%204%25%20of%20companies%20are%20hiring%20additional%20people%20and%2095%25%20are%20not%20hiring%20new%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBusiness%20confidence%20slipped%20to%20a%20five-month%20low%20amid%20concerns%20surrounding%20inflation%20and%20demand%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20survey%E2%80%99s%20new%20orders%20index%20slipped%20to%20a%20one-year%20low%2C%20as%20some%20firms%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20current%20demand%20picture%20for%20their%20products.%20Consumer%20goods%20were%20behind%20most%20of%20the%20slowdown%2C%20recording%20considerably%20softer%20increases%20in%20sales%2C%20production%2C%20exports%2C%20input%20inventories%20and%20buying%20levels%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pollyanna%20De%20Lima%2C%20economics%20associate%20director%20at%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%20Market%20Intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20saw%20further%20indication%20of%20broadly-stable%20inflationary%20forces%20across%20the%20manufacturing%20industry.%20It%20appears%20that%20a%20moderate%20increase%20in%20input%20costs%20was%20simply%20passed%20on%20to%20clients.%20Nonetheless%2C%20qualitative%20evidence%20from%20the%20future%20output%20question%20revealed%20an%20interesting%20finding%2C%20as%20reports%20of%20rising%20inflation%20expectations%20were%20expected%20to%20dent%20demand%20and%20subsequently%20production%20gr